    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-12-09T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-12-09T17:00:00-05:00" n="348"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d348">
                <head>348. Telegram 3001 from Paris, December 9<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d348fn1">Further discussion of <gloss target="#t_IMF_1">IMF</gloss>
                        borrowing arrangement. Official Use Only. 2 pp. Department of State, Central
                        Files, 398.13/12–961.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName>Paris</placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1961-12-09T17:00:00-05:00">December 9, 1961, 5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d348-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d348-1"/>
                <p>For Treasury from <persName corresp="#p_LJM_1">Leddy</persName>. Pass <persName
                        corresp="#p_SFA_1">Southard</persName>. Reference: Embtel 2963.</p>
                <p>As result discussions here December 8 and 9, draft agreement revised, made more
                    concise and converted into form of letters addressed by French Finance Minister
                    (in his capacity of Chairman Ministerial meeting) to each of other participants
                    and short replies confirming understanding as set forth in letters. Text of
                    exchange of letters, draft confirmations thereof, and suggested minute of
                    Ministers meeting to be before Ministers next week, contained in immediately
                    preceding telegram. <persName corresp="#p_JP_1">Jacobsson</persName> is cabling
                    over weekend full text of draft fund decision for distribution to EXED Board
                    members. <persName corresp="#p_SFA_1">Southard</persName> can obtain copy from
                    Fund Monday morning. Basis these documents request Treasury obtain <gloss
                        target="#t_NAC_1">NAC</gloss> telephone poll accordance Secretary’s request.
                    Concensus of meeting here December 9 that only four major questions expected to
                    be discussed by Ministers: (1) Amount of commitments of participants;</p>
                <p>(2) Duration of Fund decision (3 or 5 years);</p>
                <p>(3) Method of voting procedure (on which clear reservation only <pb facs="d348-2"
                        n="2" type="facsimile" xml:id="d348-2"/> by Netherlands);</p>
                <p>(4) Chairman of Ad Hoc Committee.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>Gavin</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
